sec.p:
To assess the potential antifungal effects of HX-140, antagonistic activity against seven phytopathogenic fungi was assessed on PDA plates by dual culture analysis as described in a previous study [45]. Three replicates were performed for each treatment and the experiments were repeated twice. The plates were incubated for 9 days in the dark at 28 °C and the antagonism was determined by measuring the zone of inhibition, the distance between the growing edges of HX-140 and fungi. The inhibition ratio was calculated using the following formula [22]:
