Disease severity of cucumber seedlings was divided into five classes and recorded using a disease index ranging from 0 to 4 as follows:
Level 0-Plant was healthy with no illness;
Level 1-Leaves with slight wilting;
Level 2-Stems and leaves slightly wilted with necrotic spots on the leaves;
Level 3-Plants moderately wilted with necrotic spots on leaves and stems;
Level 4-Plants died.

The disease index and biocontrol efficacy were calculated according to the following formulas [47]:
